<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Pleuraphis</i> <i>rigida</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Achnatherum</i> <i>hymenoides</i>, <i>Bouteloua</i> <i>eriopoda</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>rubens</i>, <i>Dalea</i> <i>mollissima</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>sarothrae</i>, <i>Panicum</i> <i>urvilleanum</i>, <i>Petalonyx</i> <i>thurberi</i> and <i>Sphaeralcea</i> <i>ambigua</i>. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover, including trees:<i>Chilopsis</i> <i>linearis</i> or <i>Yucca</i> <i>brevifolia</i> and shrubs:<i>Ambrosia</i> <i>dumosa</i>, <i>Ambrosia</i> <i>salsola</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>canescens</i>, <i>Cylindropuntia</i> <i>acanthocarpa</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Ephedra</i> <i>nevadensis</i>, <i>Larrea</i> <i>tridentata</i>, <i>Lycium</i> <i>andersonii</i>, <i>Senegalia</i> <i>greggii</i> and <i>Yucca</i> <i>schidigera</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is open to intermittent with seasonal annuals. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Pleuraphis rigida</i> â‰¥ 2% absolute cover in the herbaceous layer; herbaceous cover exceeds shrub or tree cover (Thomas et al. 2004).</li>
		
		<li><i>Pleuraphis rigida</i> 10-35% absolute cover in the herbaceous layer; emergent shrubs or trees < 10% absolute cover (Keeler-Wolf et al. 1998b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Flat ridges, lower bajadas, slopes, dune aprons, and stabilized dunes. Soils may be clayey, sandy, or rocky.  </div>
</div>

        
